mentCurrent Employee - Anonymous Employee in Vienna, VACurrent Employee - Anonymous Employee in Vienna, VARecommendsPositive OutlookI have been working at Glassman Wealth Services (More than a year)ProsThe firm does a great job of making sure that employees are happy & satisfied, with the idea that if all of the basics (compensation, benefits, healthcare, etc.) are covered, we will work even harder on behalf of what matters - our clients. So it's not a surprise that employees are thriving in their roles and working tirelessly in their pursuit of enriching our clients' lives.We've been voted a "best place to work" by Washingtonian Magazine and Washington Business Journal, deservedly so.We're known for being curious people who love what we do, and we're intentional about building a culture that fosters that curiosity, and having fun while we do it.It's a relatively young group, which is great (and somewhat rare) in the financial planning world, but that makes it a promising place to build your career.ConsAs with any small firm, everyone pitches in. Sometimes that means wearing a lot of hats, but the work is incredibly rewarding!Advice to ManagementContinue being intentional in how the firm grows, and keep building up & training our employees in the process.Share on FacebookShare on TwitterShare on WhatsAppShare via EmailCopy LinkLink Copied!Flag as InappropriateFlag as InappropriateHelpful (0) Glassman Wealth Services Response seconds agoEdit • Delete Glassman Wealth Services 2016-08-08 10:50 PDT Aug 8, 2016"Best Place to Work (for real...not just a title)"StarStarStarStarStarWork/Life BalanceCulture & ValuesCareer OpportunitiesComp & BenefitsSenior ManagementCurrent Employee - Anonymous EmployeeCurrent Employee - Anonymous EmployeeRecommendsPositive OutlookI have been working at Glassman Wealth Services full-timeProsGlassman Wealth puts a strong emphasis on culture. We have created an environment that promotes curiosity and breeds creativity. Employees genuinely enjo