Federated Investors, Inc. (FII) Downgraded by BidaskClub to Hold


					Posted by Harper Lund on Jul 27th, 2017 // No Comments




Federated Investors, Inc. (NYSE:FII) was downgraded by investment analysts at BidaskClub from a “buy” rating to a “hold” rating in a research report issued on Tuesday.
Several other research firms also recently issued reports on FII. Keefe, Bruyette & Woods  reaffirmed a “sell” rating and set a $28.00 price objective on shares of Federated Investors in a report on Friday, July 14th. Zacks Investment Research downgraded Federated Investors from a “buy” rating to a “hold” rating in a report on Thursday, July 13th. ValuEngine downgraded Federated Investors from a “buy” rating to a “hold” rating in a report on Friday, June 2nd. Finally, Royal Bank Of Canada began coverage on Federated Investors in a report on Thursday, June 29th. They set a “sector perform” rating and a $27.00 price objective on the stock. Two analysts have rated the stock with a sell rating and seven have issued  a hold rating to the company. The company currently has an average rating of “Hold” and an average price target of $24.71.


 Get Federated Investors Inc. alerts:



Shares of Federated Investors (FII) traded down 0.95% during mid-day trading on Tuesday, reaching $29.16. The company’s stock had a trading volume of 525,535 shares. The company has a 50 day moving average of $28.29 and a 200-day moving average of $26.97. The firm has a market capitalization of $2.85 billion, a P/E ratio of 14.01 and a beta of 1.41. Federated Investors has a 12 month low of $24.52 and a 12 month high of $33.13. 





Federated Investors (NYSE:FII) last announced its earnings results on Thursday, April 27th. The asset manager reported $0.49 EPS for the quarter, topping the consensus estimate of $0.47 by $0.02. The business had revenue of $273.50 million for the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $290.19 million. Federated Investors had a return on equity of 33.32% and a net margin of 18.62%. Federated Investors’s revenue was up .5% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same period in the previous year, the business earned $0.44 EPS.  Equities research analysts forecast that  Federated Investors will post $2.02 EPS for the current year. 
TRADEMARK VIOLATION NOTICE: “Federated Investors, Inc. (FII) Downgraded by BidaskClub to Hold” was first  posted by Chaffey Breeze and is owned by of Chaffey Breeze. If you are reading this piece on another domain, it was copied illegally and reposted in violation of U.S. and international trademark & copyright law. The original version of this piece can be read at https://www.chaffeybreeze.com/2017/07/27/federated-investors-inc-fii-downgraded-by-bidaskclub-to-hold.html. 
In related news, insider Richard A. Novak sold 2,700 shares of the company’s stock in a transaction on Friday, June 23rd. The shares were sold at an average price of $27.70, for a total value of $74,790.00. Following the completion of the sale, the insider now owns 44,741 shares in the company, valued at approximately $1,239,325.70. The transaction was disclosed in a filing with the SEC, which is available through this link. Corporate insiders own  7.10% of the company’s stock. 
Several hedge funds have recently added to or reduced their stakes in FII. Tyers Asset Management LLC boosted its stake in  Federated Investors by 12.7% in the first quarter. Tyers Asset Management LLC now owns 3,916 shares of the asset manager’s stock worth $103,000 after buying an additional 440 shares in the last quarter.  Zurcher Kantonalbank Zurich Cantonalbank boosted its stake in  Federated Investors by 60.7% in the first quarter. Zurcher Kantonalbank Zurich Cantonalbank now owns 4,126 shares of the asset manager’s stock worth $109,000 after buying an additional 1,559 shares in the last quarter.  First Bank & Trust boosted its stake in  Federated Investors by 16.9% in the first quarter. First Bank & Trust now owns 4,346 shares of the asset manager’s stock worth $115,000 after buying an additional 627 shares in the last quarter.  Flinton Capital Management LLC boosted its stake in  Federated Investors by 12.7% in the first quarter. Flinton Capital Management LLC now owns 4,984 shares of the asset manager’s stock worth $131,000 after buying an additional 560 shares in the last quarter.  Finally, FNY Partners Fund LP purchased a new stake in  Federated Investors during the first quarter worth approximately $131,000. Institutional investors and hedge funds own  84.79% of the company’s stock. 
About Federated Investors
Federated Investors, Inc (Federated) is a provider of investment management products and related financial services. Federated operates through investment management business segment. It is engaged in sponsoring, marketing and providing investment-related services to various investment products, including mutual funds and Separate Accounts, which include separately managed accounts, institutional accounts, sub-advised funds and other managed products.







